parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to accidents, strandings, and safety risks.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty when the tank is full
or remains stuck on empty; the low fuel light comes on even when the tank is full; the gauge needle moves erratically; the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke and flames under the dashboard
power windows and door locks malfunctioning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failures can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or failing to start
passenger side air bag warning light illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Door lock and window malfunctions can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and accidents.
symptoms: Door locks and windows not functioning
intermittent functionality of door locks and windows

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system malfunctions can cause fuel leaks, fires, and accidents, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: tank empty warning light coming on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Remote Starter and Anti-Theft System Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Remote starter and anti-theft system malfunctions can cause inconvenience and safety risks.
The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at night.
symptoms: The headlights suddenly go out or dim
and sometimes staying off; the failure can occur intermittently
with no specific pattern or warning; the high beam lights may also be affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight module can cause the headlights to fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: the headlight module melts into the fuse box
and the fuses may be damaged; the failure can occur suddenly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailable recall repairs can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives notification of a recall
but the parts needed for the repair are unavailable or take an excessive amount of time to arrive; the vehicle owner may experience the failure before the repair can be made.
